I am not sure if "no deprecation" is appropriate; my understanding is that the tendency is more towards "always provide one". In any case, it shouldn't be hard to add a `@[deprecated (since := "yyyy-mm-dd")] alias old_name := new_name` for the three renamed results.

Please do not remove the aligns; instead change them to the new name. (Also below.)

I guess I don't understand the point of aliasing or aligning things when the types have changed. Even with the alias it's still a breaking change. Any code that relied on `nthLe` will be broken with this change either way. I'll readd the old lemmas with aligns and add a deprecated tag on them

Oh nevermind, I didn't realize `nthLe` is now defined in terms of `get`. So it probably wouldn't be a breaking change? But it still seems like a bad idea to align to something with a (syntactically) different type. I've readded the old lemmas.
